name: First Visit! Air Canada New Livery 777-233LR [C-FIUJ] Landing and Takeoff at Calgary Airport
description:
As part of what is known as the busiest travel day of the year, Air Canada sent a 777-200LR on the regular Toronto-Calgary-Toronto route, along with a myriad of other heavies, a route that's one of the busiest domestic routes out of Calgary but is normally served with narrowbody aircraft. Much to the luck of YYC spotters, the aircraft operating the flight happened to be one of the three 777s that Air Canada has painted in their new livery revealed earlier this year! Here we have the first visit of a 777 in Air Canada's new livery at YYC Calgary International Airport, landing on 35R and then departing again a few hours later. ATC is included, hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
